<br>
The fact is, I KNOW the people who are speed looters and loot whores ( yes, you bastages whom say you need something you don't! ).  I avoid them at all cost.  Wich means I can't do pickup groups in OS.  Damn near every group has a greedy player I knew from the past.<br>
<br>
Now the upside is that after 49+ levels, people WANT their cleric to be well equiped, not die, and have plenty of cash for DOTs to keep their dumb asses alive.  So usually Clerics get Money and DOTs from their guilds and friends.  <br>
<br>
And I SWEAR, no druids should even touch the topic of greed ....<br>
<br>
FYI:  I will stay 12 hours in OS and cast Symbol the whole time with no compensation.  I won't even be upset.  However, don't expect me to join your group again.  Furthurmore, its only when Im glutton for punishment that I will grab a pickup group in OS.  At least I know my guildies are not greedy loot whores out to scam their way into loot they do not need.<br>
<br>
 <p>Lorentic HealiningHands - 56 Cleric of Tunare<BR>
Wreeaath Bringer - 56 Enchanter who believes in Nothing<BR>
Upside YourHead - 48 Monk who thinks he is invinceable<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usagemonprayeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sagemon Prayeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 340<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/20/02 1:17:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much compensation do clerics require?</span><hr size=1> To answer the original question, the arrangement was NOT reasonable.  Even if you had a few deaths, there is no way that the cleric used more than a stack of periodots casting Aego over a four hour period.  I'm guessing that your cleric walked away with several hundred plat in gems above and beyond periodot costs.<br>
<br>
This is a touchy issue that has been on this board many times.  Unfortunately, there are some clerics who make a lot of money on gems and who feel that it is an entitlement.  On the other hand, there are a lot of people who will undercompensate the cleric.  The person who said to just give the cleric the first two or three gems is one of those people.  Depending on the value of the gems, the number of dispels/deaths, and the type of spell being using (Naltron, Marzin, or Aegolism), that could cover the cleric's costs for less than an hour.<br>
<br>
Back when I was in a lot of pickup groups, I was usually the master looter.  I used to shock people by passing out a lot of extra gems in a zone like OS.  A fair number of people would refuse to take them from me, saying that I lost money in other zones.  They were right.  I sometimes took big losses in zones like KC, Chardok, and The Hole, not to mention pickup raids to places like Sky and Fear.  Over time, it probably evened out.<br>
<br>
I've never been obsessed with money.  I never ask for more gems than is necessary to cover my costs, I try to make sure that some of the gems get to the enchanter if Rune is being used, and I never accept payment for a rez.  However, I know that a lot of clerics have a different perspective, and I can't say that they're unjustified.  Clerics <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> get screwed on periodot costs a lot.  There just isn't an easy answer to this issue, other than simply avoiding pickup groups. <p>Sagemon Prayeth<BR>
