</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utoein.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toein</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/21/02 2:47:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much compensation do clerics require?</span><hr size=1> I ML alot when im in OS. I have absolutly no problem with giving the first 3 to 5 cash loots to the cleric (this very easily can add up to 500pp). Spell drops in Necro are for the most part not needed by people in group for thier mains (at least in the groups ive been in at necro). So I pass them out much like cash loots (many of those spells can be turned into a NPC in FV and can then be sold for up to 500pp, and many can be sold to merchants for up to 30pp each, that can add up fast). I always do an even split of cash all the way down to silver. Clerics should be paid, but I personally don't think they should get all the gems. Why would I be there beside xp, unless I had the chance to get gems.<br>
<br>
I realize it does not cost me plat to camp in any dungeon, but if people didn't get treasure, they wouldn't bother going to places like that.<br>
<br>
These are never easy subjects, cause everyone wants something. It can easily degenerate into nothing but a fight.<br>
<br>
I have seen some clerics insist on all the cash loot gems, and in one instance it would have added up to well over 2k.<br>
<br>
There are no easy answers, and no way to make everyone happy.<br>
