<br>
That can also be as little as 120 pp.  120 pp = less than 10 periodots = not enough to keep Symbol of Naltron or Marzin up for more than an hour.  Unless you're an expert on the value of cash loot gems, you're probably one of the people who screw over clerics, even though you didn't realize it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Spell drops in Necro are for the most part not needed by people in group for thier mains (at least in the groups ive been in at necro). So I pass them out much like cash loots (many of those spells can be turned into a NPC in FV and can then be sold for up to 500pp, and many can be sold to merchants for up to 30pp each, that can add up fast).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As far as I'm concerned, the value of a spell drop is what a vendor will pay for it, which is about 10 to 15 pp on average.  I don't hang out in EC auctioning spells, and I've never seen a merchant pay 30 pp for any sub-55 spell.  If I've used a full stack of periodots, it would take about 20 drops spells to compensate me.  If you tried to tell me that the spells are worth more than that, I'd tell you to kiss my ass.<br>
<br>
There are people who make money selling the sub-55 spells, but it requires an investment of time that I don't choose to make.  When I wind up with extra spells, they either get sold to the first merchant I see or dumped into my guild's spell bank.<br>
<br>
As a couple other people have commented, Symbol probably gets cast too much in experience groups.  Not everyone really needs it.  You need it on the main tank, the enchanter, and the shaman/necro if they're converting HPs to mana.  For everyone else, it's a luxury, albeit a useful luxury.  If you don't want Symbol, just speak up. <p>Sagemon Prayeth<BR>
High Priest of Quellious the Tranquil<BR>A Twist of Fate</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udesbarolis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Desbarolis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 574<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/21/02 6:54:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much compensation do clerics require?</span><hr size=1> You know what gets to me ... is that I'm constantly having to pay a cleric for symbol's in my own groups.  They get compensated with things that drop in the zone typically -- although in zones like Akheva Ruins, one place I love to frequent, I don't have a problem paying the cleric since there isn't much if anything dropping to compensate them with -- so I shouldn't have to pay them for it.  ESPECIALLY if I'm the one doing crowd control, or pulling.<br>
<br>
Not many things bug me more than an inefficient cleric.  If I'm pulling, I'm taking harmtouches for ~6-700 damage, being beat on for 80-150 damage a pop while running back, and have to take a beating for 3-5 seconds while the main tank gets aggro off me.  Best case scenario in a place like chardok, I'll take 6-800 damage per pull.  In a bad case I'll take as much as 12-1300 damage, worste case sometimes as much as 1800 damage.  So what makes the most sense?  Why, remedy or divine light of course!  Don't symbol the puller so you can complete heal them, that doesn't make sense ;p<br>
<br>
-Desbarolis -- 60th Virtuoso <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unurbus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nurbus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/25/02 6:11:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much compensation do clerics require?</span><hr size=1> I think clerics should get non quest gems but ive always made a habbit of offering around 20-50pp with my sk to a cleric when i join the group and no one has ever accepted it =) btw i only read the first page of post! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udraelyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Draelyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/25/02 7:23:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3073.topic&index=70>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How much compensation do clerics require?</span><hr size=1> Obviously my system isn't the most reliable, it *can* leave the cleric obscenely under compensated, and perhaps cause bitterness in the group to be compensated based on a performance only aspect. I still do think it would force people to actually pay attention and learn their class. <br>
<br>
